a strong desire for power,

112
00:07:05,468 --> 00:07:07,845
who'll probably use the notebook
only for his own personal gain.

113
00:07:10,973 --> 00:07:14,560
Misa will be released from
her confinement if you do that.

114
00:07:15,227 --> 00:07:18,147
If she is not released
after several years, kill me.

115
00:07:18,898 --> 00:07:19,941
How does that sound?

116
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:23,736
Light Yagami,
what are you thinking?

117
00:07:24,445 --> 00:07:27,448
This is to save Misa.
Trust me.

118
00:07:32,244 --> 00:07:36,415
All right. If Misa will be saved
I'll do as you ask.

119
00:07:38,542 --> 00:07:41,420
Later, I'll make sure
to be confined like Misa

120
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:44,757
and put under 24-hour surveillance.

121
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:48,844
While in confinement, I will
relinquish ownership of the notebook,

122
00:07:49,428 --> 00:07:52,098
and lose all memory of
the Death Note.

123
00:07:53,265 --> 00:07:56,102
During that time, the killings
of criminals will begin again.

124
00:07:56,519 --> 00:07:58,187
If that continues,

125
00:07:58,479 --> 00:08:01,232
Ryuzaki will have to release
the both of us sooner or later.

126
00:08:03,901 --> 00:08:08,572
Since I've lost all my memory,
I'll probably try to catch Kira...

127
00:08:10,074 --> 00:08:11,534
Since that's
the kind of person I am.

128
00:08:12,618 --> 00:08:15,621
And you'll try to catch the guy
who Rem gives the notebook to

129
00:08:15,705 --> 00:08:18,290
and steal the notebook
before L gets to him.

130
00:08:18,708 --> 00:08:19,834
That's right.

131
00:08:19,917 --> 00:08:22,253
And at that time, I'll kill
the owner of the notebook.

132
00:08:23,462 --> 00:08:24,755
But there is one problem...

133
00:08:26,090 --> 00:08:27,967
If you don't have ownership
of the notebook,

134
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:31,637
your memory will only return
while you're touching the notebook.

135
00:08:32,013 --> 00:08:35,016
Once you let go, your memory
will disappear.

136
00:08:38,394 --> 00:08:42,148
<i>I'll kill Higuchi without
letting go of this notebook!</i>

137
00:08:42,815 --> 00:08:44,900
<i>If I do that, ownership will
transfer back to me and...</i>

138
00:08:45,401 --> 00:08:46,569
<i>my memory won't disappear!</i>

139
00:08:50,114 --> 00:08:53,492
<i>I have to pull here four times
within a second...</i>

140
00:08:54,285 --> 00:08:55,369
<i>All right...</i>

141
00:08:55,661 --> 00:08:57,913
<i>I was wearing this watch.</i>

142
00:08:58,956 --> 00:09:00,666
<i>Habits don't change.</i>

143
00:09:12,845 --> 00:09:15,347
Mr. Yagami, take Higuchi
to the car.

144
00:09:16,849 --> 00:09:18,768
All right! Understood!

145
00:09:21,562 --> 00:09:22,813
KYOSUKE HIGUCHI

146
00:09:27,568 --> 00:09:28,611
This notebook...

147
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:32,239
What do you suppose we'll find
if we have it scientifically analyzed?

148
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,700
That's not like you.

149
00:09:35,367 --> 00:09:37,203
That thing is beyond science.

150
00:09:38,829 --> 00:09:39,955
That's true...

151
00:09:52,259 --> 00:09:55,763
<i>This is the longest forty
seconds of my life...</i>

152
00:10:12,780 --> 00:10:13,781
Higuchi?!

153
00:10:13,864 --> 00:10:14,990
Ryuzaki, Higuchi is...!

154
00:10:15,574 --> 00:10:17,159
W What?!
hat S going on?!

155
00:10:19,745 --> 00:10:20,788
Hey, Higuchi!

156
00:10:22,039 --> 00:10:23,415
What are you doing, Dad?!

157
00:10:23,916 --> 00:10:26,001
If Higuchi dies, now...

158
00:10:26,544 --> 00:10:27,878
<i>Impossible!</i>

159
00:10:28,587 --> 00:10:31,048
<i>No, but, he's already...</i>

160
00:10:33,551 --> 00:10:35,386
<i>Yeah, he's dead.</i>

161
00:10:37,012 --> 00:10:38,222
<i>Ryuzaki...</i>

162
00:10:40,182 --> 00:10:41,225
<i>you're next.</i>

163
00:11:20,264 --> 00:11:21,599
How to use it...

164
00:11:23,267 --> 00:11:27,438
The human whose name
is written in this note shall...die.

165
00:11:28,314 --> 00:11:29,398
This note will not take effect unless

166
00:11:29,481 --> 00:11:31,901
the writer has the person's face in
their mind when writing his/her name.

167
00:11:32,735 --> 00:11:37,072
Therefore, people sharing
the same name will not be affected.

168
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:39,950
If the cause of death
is written

169
00:11:40,117 --> 00:11:42,286
within 40 seconds of writing
the person's name,

170
00:11:42,369 --> 00:11:43,454
it will happen.

171
00:11:44,121 --> 00:11:45,372
If the cause of death
is not specified,

172
00:11:45,456 --> 00:11:47,291
the person will simply
die of a heart attack.

173
00:11:49,627 --> 00:11:52,296
After writing the cause of death,
details of the death should be written...

174
00:11:52,421 --> 00:11:55,966
in the next 6 minutes and 40 seconds.

175
00:12:01,013 --> 00:12:04,058
Additionally...
on the back cover's instructions...

176
00:12:06,227 --> 00:12:09,355
If you make this note unusable
by tearing it up or burning it,

177
00:12:09,897 --> 00:12:13,192
all the humans who have touched
the note until then will die.

178
00:12:13,692 --> 00:12:14,735
What?!

179
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:16,445
Is that true, Aizawa?!

180
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:18,197
<i>- Yeah, that's whafs wfltten.
- That's right. With a rule like that,</i>

181
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:19,907
- <i>No</i> way! Why <i>didn't you tell me before?
- Father and the others</i>

182
00:12:19,990 --> 00:12:21,492
- <i>How was</i> I <i>supposed to know?!</i>
- <i>Won't fly f0 cfllspose of i2'</i>

183
00:12:21,575 --> 00:12:23,619
<i>and I won't lose my memory of this.</i>

184
00:12:26,121 --> 00:12:28,666
Rem, there's no way that
the old man will get mad at us

185
00:12:28,832 --> 00:12:30,960
if we write a fake rule
here, will he?

186
00:12:31,335 --> 00:12:33,671
No. There are no such
rules against doing so.

187
00:12:34,755 --> 00:12:38,133
Fine then.
Light, you owe me apples.

188
00:12:41,470 --> 00:12:43,264
Man, I shouldn't have
touched it just

189
00:12:43,347 --> 00:12:45,140
because I wanted
to see the Shinigami.

190
00:12:45,724 --> 00:12:47,226
Then you'd be the only one

191
00:12:47,851 --> 00:12:49,520
who wouldn't know what was
going on in the investigation.

192
00:12:50,145 --> 00:12:51,188
Would you be okay with that?

193
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:55,734
No, I want to work on the same terms
as everyone else. Yes.

194
00:12:56,902 --> 00:12:59,154
And...
this last sentence...

195
00:13:02,616 --> 00:13:05,327
If the person using
the note fails to...

196
00:13:05,786 --> 00:13:08,163
consecutively write names
of people to be killed

197
00:13:08,497 --> 00:13:10,958
within 13 days of each other...

198
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:13,335
Then the user,

199
00:13:14,461 --> 00:13:15,713
will die.

200
00:13:17,965 --> 00:13:19,967
What? Which means that...

201
00:13:20,175 --> 00:13:23,637
Light and Misa-Misa are
completely cleared!

202
00:13:23,887 --> 00:13:25,222
Yes, indeed...

203
00:13:25,848 --> 00:13:27,558
Light and Amane were detained
for more than fifty days

204
00:13:27,766 --> 00:13:30,144
and are still under surveillance.

205
00:13:31,020 --> 00:13:33,522
There's no way they'd still be
alive if they're both Kira.

206
00:13:34,231 --> 00:13:35,899
Aren't you glad, Chief?!

207
00:13:36,150 --> 00:13:37,192
Yeah.

208
00:13:38,527 --> 00:13:39,528
Rem...

209
00:13:40,237 --> 00:13:41,697
...was it?
You, the white-colored Shinigami.

210
00:13:42,364 --> 00:13:45,492
Ryuzaki! That's rude!
Referring to it by it's skin color...

211
00:13:45,576 --> 00:13:46,702
Yes, it is...

212
00:13:47,536 --> 00:13:50,080
There are other notebooks in
the Human World, aren't there?

213
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:56,253
Who knows? There may be.
There may not be.

214
00:13:57,171 --> 00:14:02,009
If there were other notebooks,
are all their rules the same?

215
00:14:02,593 --> 00:14:03,761
<i>It's useless, Ryuzaki...</i>

216
00:14:04,511 --> 00:14:06,930
<i>You can't break this rule with Rem.</i>

217
00:14:07,598 --> 00:14:08,974
Yeah, they're the same.

218
00:14:09,767 --> 00:14:12,061
There are many notebooks
in the Shinigami Realm,

219
00:14:12,269 --> 00:14:13,937
but their rules are all the same.

220
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,482
Even the rules for when
humans obtain them.

221
00:14:17,399 --> 00:14:18,484
Ryuzaki...

222
00:14:19,276 --> 00:14:21,570
Light and Amane are cleared now.

223
00:14:22,196 --> 00:14:23,489
Their surveillance is over.

224
00:14:24,114 --> 00:14:26,408
That's right. It's already clear.

225
00:14:28,327 --> 00:14:29,453
You're right...

226
00:14:40,506 --> 00:14:41,548
I understand.

227
00:14:43,634 --> 00:14:45,302
I'm very sorry about everything
that's happened until now.

228
00:14:49,223 --> 00:14:50,391
Thank goodness...

229
00:14:50,599 --> 00:14:54,978
Yeah, but we still can't say
that we've solved the case.

230
00:14:55,396 --> 00:14:57,064
I want these handcuffs removed,

231
00:14:57,147 --> 00:14:58,607
but can I continue to
investigate here?

232
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:00,776
Yes...

233
00:15:02,194 --> 00:15:05,614
<i>Misa and I are now
completely cleared...</i>

234
00:15:06,532 --> 00:15:09,910
<i>He has no choice but to believe
the fake rule that was written</i>

235
00:15:10,661 --> 00:15:12,413
<i>by a Shinigami into
the notebook of death...</i>

236
00:15:13,497 --> 00:15:15,624
<i>With the fake rules that I made up...</i>

237
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:17,543
<i>Ryuzaki's lost his edge.</i>

238
00:15:18,794 --> 00:15:19,920
<i>Listen, Ryuzaki...</i>

239
00:15:20,754 --> 00:15:25,008
<i>In any world, rules are always
created by those who are gods.</i>

240
00:15:25,509 --> 00:15:28,053
